{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1779254373231,"sessionID":"ses_1bc338abcffeFT9IMQYKVjO1Hs","part":{"type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"call_00_GInNqEE2p5LfVUFbTFBZ8330","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude-project/nestfind/status/CONTRACT_VALIDATION.md"},"output":"<path>/Users/saifulpotential/Potential/nestfind-sample/.claude-project/nestfind/status/CONTRACT_VALIDATION.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: phase: integrate-contract-validation\n2: dtos_checked: 14\n3: forms_checked: 13\n4: mismatches_found: 1\n5: \n6: ## Mismatches\n7: \n8: | DTO | Field | Backend Expects | Frontend Sends | Severity |\n9: |-----|-------|-----------------|----------------|----------|\n10: | `CreatePropertyDto` / `UpdatePropertyDto` | `address` | Nested object: `{ street: string, city: string, state: string, zipCode: string, latitude?: number, longitude?: number }` (`backend/src/modules/properties/dto/create-property.dto.ts:96`) | Flat top-level fields: `addressStreet`, `addressCity`, `addressState`, `addressZipCode` (`frontend/app/pages/admin/property-form.tsx:36-39`) | **HIGH** |\n11: \n12: **Root cause:** The backend `CreatePropertyDto` defines address as a nested `AddressDto` with `@ValidateNested()` (line 94). The backend service `flattenAddress()` at `backend/src/modules/properties/property.service.ts:200-208` expects to receive a nested `address` object and flattens it for the entity. The frontend type `CreatePropertyDto` (`frontend/app/types/api/property.d.ts:72-88`) defines flat address fields because the API response returns them flat (the entity stores them flat: `addressStreet`, `addressCity`, etc. in `backend/src/modules/properties/entities/property.entity.ts:49`). This mismatch means property creation will fail with a validation error because the required nested `address` field is missing from the request body.\n13: \n14: ## Matched Contracts\n15: \n16: | DTO | Fields | Status |\n17: |-----|--------|--------|\n18: | `RegisterDto` (extends `CreateUserDto`) | `name`, `email`, `password`, `phone?` — `signup.tsx:34-38` maps `fullName→name`, sends all fields. `register.tsx:35` sends `name`, `email`, `password` (phone omitted, optional so OK). | MATCH |\n19: | `LoginDto` | `email`, `password` — `login.tsx:27` via `LoginFormData`. `admin-login.tsx:12` sends `{email, password}`. | MATCH |\n20: | `ForgotPasswordDto` | `email` — `forgot-password.tsx:14` sends `{email}`. | MATCH |\n21: | `ResetPasswordDto` | `token`, `password` — `reset-password.tsx:25` sends `{token, password: data.newPassword}`. | MATCH |\n22: | `SubmitInquiryDto` | `message`, `name?`, `email?`, `phone?` — `detail.tsx:45-52` sends all fields correctly. | MATCH |\n23: | `RespondInquiryDto` | `response` — `admin/inquiries.tsx:27` sends `{response}`. | MATCH |\n24: | `UpdateUserStatusDto` | `status: 'active' \\| 'suspended'` — `admin/users.tsx:18` sends correct values matching `UserStatusEnum`. | MATCH |\n25: | `CreateFavoriteDto` | `propertyId` — `search.tsx:97`, `detail.tsx:35` send `{propertyId}`. | MATCH |\n26: | `CreateAmenityDto` | `name`, `icon` — `frontend/app/services/api/amenityService.ts:4-7` matches backend `create-amenity.dto.ts`. | MATCH |\n27: | `UpdateAmenityDto` | `name?`, `icon?` — `frontend/app/services/api/amenityService.ts:9-12` PartialType matches backend. | MATCH |\n28: | `ReorderPhotosDto` | `photoIds: string[]` — `frontend/app/services/api/propertyService.ts:41` sends `{photoIds}`. | MATCH |\n29: | `UpdateProfileDto` (subset of `UpdateUserDto`) | `name?`, `phone?` — `profile.tsx:33-34` sends correct subset. Backend accepts `email?`, `role?`, `status?` too, but omitting them is fine (all optional). | MATCH |\n30: \n31: ## Audit Notes\n32: \n33: - **PropertyTypeEnum values** match: frontend `PROPERTY_TYPES = ['apartment', 'house', 'condo', 'townhouse', 'studio']` (`frontend/app/types/api/property.d.ts:1`) vs backend `PropertyTypeEnum` (`backend/src/common/enums/property-type.enum.ts`).\n34: - **UserStatusEnum values** match: frontend `'active' | 'suspended'` vs backend `UserStatusEnum.ACTIVE = 'active'`, `UserStatusEnum.SUSPENDED = 'suspended'`.\n35: - **RoleEnum values** match: frontend `'renter' | 'admin'` vs backend `RoleEnum.RENTER = 'renter'`, `RoleEnum.ADMIN = 'admin'`.\n36: - **InquiryStatus values** match: frontend `'new' | 'read' | 'responded'` vs backend `InquiryStatusEnum`.\n37: - **Two registration forms** exist: `register.tsx` (minimal, 3 fields) and `signup.tsx` (full, 4 fields incl. phone). Both correctly map to `RegisterDto`.\n38: - **Dead code**: `utils/validations/auth.ts` exports `registerSchema` and `RegisterFormData` but no form uses them — both registration forms define their own inline zod schemas.\n39: - **search.tsx property type dropdown** omits `studio` as a property type filter option, but handles studios via the bedrooms dropdown (bedrooms=0 \"Studio\"). This is a UI design choice, not a contract mismatch.\n40: - **login.tsx** has a `rememberMe` checkbox but this state is not sent to the API — it's client-only UI with no backend contract.\n41: - **No latitude/longitude inputs** exist in `property-form.tsx` but these are optional in `AddressDto`, so no mismatch.\n\n(End of file - total 41 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"phase: integrate-contract-validation\ndtos_checked: 14\nforms_checked: 13\nmismatches_found: 1\n\n## Mismatches\n\n| DTO | Field | Backend Expects | Frontend Sends | Severity |\n|-----|-------|-----------------|----------------|----------|\n| `CreatePropertyDto` / `UpdatePropertyDto` | `address` | Nested object: `{ street: string, city: string, state: string, zipCode: string, latitude?: number, longitude?: number }` (`backend/src/modules/properties/dto/create-property.dto.ts:96`) | Flat top-level fields: `addressStreet`, `addressCity`, `addressState`, `addressZipCode` (`frontend/app/pages/admin/property-form.tsx:36-39`) | **HIGH** |\n\n**Root cause:** The backend `CreatePropertyDto` defines address as a nested `AddressDto` with `@ValidateNested()` (line 94). The backend service `flattenAddress()` at `backend/src/modules/properties/property.service.ts:200-208` expects to receive a nested `address` object and flattens it for the entity. The frontend type `CreatePropertyDto` (`frontend/app/types/api/property.d.ts:72-88`) defines flat address fields because the API response returns them flat (the entity stores them flat: `addressStreet`, `addressCity`, etc. in `backend/src/modules/properties/entities/property.entity.ts:49`). This mismatch means property creation will fail with a validation error because the required nested `address` field is missing from the request body.\n\n## Matched Contracts\n\n| DTO | Fields | Status |\n|-----|--------|--------|\n| `RegisterDto` (extends `CreateUserDto`) | `name`, `email`, `password`, `phone?` — `signup.tsx:34-38` maps `fullName→name`, sends all fields. `register.tsx:35` sends `name`, `email`, `password` (phone omitted, optional so OK). | MATCH |\n| `LoginDto` | `email`, `password` — `login.tsx:27` via `LoginFormData`. `admin-login.tsx:12` sends `{email, password}`. | MATCH |\n| `ForgotPasswordDto` | `email` — `forgot-password.tsx:14` sends `{email}`. | MATCH |","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":".claude-project/nestfind/status/CONTRACT_VALIDATION.md","time":{"start":1779254372952,"end":1779254373230}},"id":"prt_e43d3243b001Hvo2zJC6oQOm3U","sessionID":"ses_1bc338abcffeFT9IMQYKVjO1Hs","messageID":"msg_e43d30a240013C8r54KftxLdpK"}}
